<div class="legal-page-container">
    <!-- Header with logo -->
    <div class="legal-header">
        <!-- ... resto del contenido ... -->
        <img src="/img/logo-nutris_xl.jpg" alt="Nutris Logo" class="legal-logo" />
        <h1 class="legal-title">Internal Reporting System Policy</h1>
        <p class="legal-subtitle">Whistleblower Channel - Nutris Group</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Main content -->
    <div class="legal-content">

        <!-- 1. PURPOSE -->
        <section class="legal-section">
            <h2 class="section-title">1. PURPOSE</h2>
            <p>
                In order to foster a culture of information and communication as a mechanism to prevent and detect conduct constituting
                crimes, and in compliance with Law 2/2023 of February 20, regulating the protection of persons who report regulatory
                infringements and combating corruption, <strong>NUTRIS INGREDIENTES, S.L.</strong> and <strong>ROYPAS BY NUTRIS, S.A.U.</strong>
                (hereinafter <strong>NUTRIS GROUP</strong>) have established an Internal Reporting System.
            </p>
            <p>
                The purpose of this Policy is to regulate the NUTRIS GROUP's Internal Reporting System, and together with its Ethical
                Channel Management Procedure, to guarantee professional, confidential, impartial, and maximum protection management
                throughout the process, thereby generating a climate of trust for its stakeholders.
            </p>
        </section>

        <!-- 2. SCOPE -->
        <section class="legal-section">
            <h2 class="section-title">2. SCOPE</h2>

            <h3 class="subsection-title">2.1. Material Scope</h3>
            <p>
                Information processed through the Internal Reporting System will refer to serious misconduct or suspected corruption,
                which may constitute serious or very serious criminal or administrative offenses related to NUTRIS GROUP's activities,
                which the informant has observed or about which they have received information in the course of their work or professional
                relationship with NUTRIS GROUP.
            </p>

            <div class="info-box">
                <h4>Information will refer to:</h4>
                <ul class="legal-list">
                    <li>
                        <strong>a) Infringements within the scope of application of European Union acts:</strong>
                        <ul class="nested-list">
                            <li>Public procurement</li>
                            <li>Financial services, products and markets, and prevention of money laundering and terrorist financing</li>
                            <li>Product safety and compliance</li>
                            <li>Transport safety</li>
                            <li>Environmental protection</li>
                            <li>Protection against radiation and nuclear safety</li>
                            <li>Food and feed safety, animal health and welfare</li>
                            <li>Public health</li>
                            <li>Consumer protection</li>
                            <li>Protection of privacy and personal data, and security of network and information systems</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>b) Infringements affecting the financial interests of the European Union</strong>
                        as contemplated in Article 325 of the Treaty on the Functioning of the European Union (TFEU).
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>c) Infringements affecting the internal market</strong>, as contemplated in Article 26, paragraph 2
                        of the TFEU, including infringements of European Union rules on competition and State aid.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>d) Actions or omissions</strong> that may constitute serious or very serious criminal or administrative
                        offenses, including those offenses that imply economic damage to the Public Treasury and Social Security.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>e) Infringements of labor law</strong> regarding health and safety at work reported by workers.
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <h3 class="subsection-title">2.2. Personal Scope</h3>
            <p>
                The Internal Reporting System will allow communications to be made by persons who, in a work or professional context,
                are aware of the infringements provided for in section 2.1., including in all cases:
            </p>
            <ul class="legal-list">
                <li>Employees, volunteers, interns, and workers in training periods</li>
                <li>Self-employed persons</li>
                <li>Shareholders, partners, and persons belonging to the administration, management, or supervision body of the company</li>
                <li>Anyone working for or under the supervision and direction of contractors, subcontractors, and suppliers</li>
                <li>Persons whose employment relationship has not yet begun, when information was obtained during the selection process</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 class="subsection-title">2.3. Corporate Scope</h3>
            <p>
                This Policy applies to the companies of NUTRIS GROUP:
                <strong>NUTRIS INGREDIENTS, S.L.</strong> and <strong>ROYPAS BY NUTRIS, S.A.U.</strong>
            </p>
        </section>

        <!-- 3. DEFINITIONS -->
        <section class="legal-section">
            <h2 class="section-title">3. DEFINITIONS</h2>
            <dl class="definitions-list">
                <dt>Internal Reporting System</dt>
                <dd>
                    System composed of the internal communication channel (Ethical Channel), the system manager, a policy that sets out
                    the general principles of the system, and procedures establishing how to manage and follow up on received information.
                </dd>

                <dt>Information on infringements</dt>
                <dd>
                    Information, including reasonable suspicions, about actual or potential infringements that have occurred or are very
                    likely to occur in the organization.
                </dd>

                <dt>Report</dt>
                <dd>The communication of information on infringements.</dd>

                <dt>Reporting person or informant</dt>
                <dd>
                    Natural person who communicates information on infringements obtained in the context of their work or professional activities.
                </dd>

                <dt>Affected person</dt>
                <dd>
                    Natural or legal person referred to in the report as the person to whom the infringement is attributed or with whom
                    it is associated.
                </dd>

                <dt>Work context</dt>
                <dd>
                    Present or past work activities through which persons can obtain information on infringements and in which these persons
                    could suffer retaliation if they communicate such information.
                </dd>

                <dt>Act of retaliation</dt>
                <dd>
                    Any acts or omissions prohibited by law that involve unfavorable treatment for persons because of their status as informants.
                </dd>

                <dt>Competent authority</dt>
                <dd>
                    Independent Authority for the Protection of the Informant (A.A.I.) or competent regional authorities or bodies.
                </dd>
            </dl>
        </section>

        <!-- 4. GUIDING PRINCIPLES -->
        <section class="legal-section">
            <h2 class="section-title">4. GUIDING PRINCIPLES</h2>
            <p>
                The procedure for receiving, processing, resolving, and recording reports received in NUTRIS GROUP's Internal Reporting
                System will be governed by the following principles:
            </p>

            <div class="principles-grid">
                <div class="principle-card">
                    <h4>Anonymity</h4>
                    <p>
                        The informant may request anonymity when submitting their report, while maintaining the possibility of two-way
                        communication with the Channel Manager.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="principle-card">
                    <h4>Good Faith</h4>
                    <p>
                        Communications will be made honestly, with conviction regarding the truth or accuracy of their subject matter,
                        providing all available data and documents.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="principle-card">
                    <h4>Information</h4>
                    <p>
                        The informant will have the right to know the processing status of their report and the investigation results.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="principle-card">
                    <h4>Confidentiality</h4>
                    <p>
                        Actions will be carried out with the utmost prudence and discretion to guarantee confidentiality regarding
                        the informant's identity.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="principle-card">
                    <h4>Data Protection</h4>
                    <p>
                        Mechanisms comply with current data protection regulations and information security standards.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="principle-card">
                    <h4>Diligence</h4>
                    <p>
                        Investigation and resolution must be carried out without undue delay, in the shortest possible time while
                        respecting due guarantees.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="principle-card">
                    <h4>Prevention of Conflict of Interest</h4>
                    <p>
                        The process is carried out by an independent, impartial, and objective team, removing conflicted members.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="principle-card">
                    <h4>Contradiction</h4>
                    <p>
                        The procedure guarantees an impartial hearing and fair treatment for all affected persons.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="principle-card">
                    <h4>Prohibition of Retaliation</h4>
                    <p>
                        Acts constituting retaliation against persons who submit a report are expressly prohibited.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="principle-card">
                    <h4>Independence</h4>
                    <p>
                        The System Manager performs their functions independently and autonomously, without receiving instructions.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="principle-card">
                    <h4>Presumption of Innocence</h4>
                    <p>
                        Affected persons will have the presumption of innocence and the right of defense throughout the process.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="principle-card">
                    <h4>Proportionality</h4>
                    <p>
                        All notifications will be treated equally, regardless of who the sender is.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- 5. RIGHTS AND GUARANTEES -->
        <section class="legal-section">
            <h2 class="section-title">5. RIGHTS AND GUARANTEES OF THE INFORMANT AND REPORTED PERSON</h2>

            <div class="two-columns">
                <div class="column">
                    <h3 class="subsection-title">5.1. Informant's Rights</h3>
                    <ul class="legal-list">
                        <li>To submit information in writing and decide whether to do so anonymously</li>
                        <li>To have anonymity maintained throughout the procedure</li>
                        <li>To have their identity not revealed to the reported person or third parties</li>
                        <li>To indicate an address or email to receive communications</li>
                        <li>To appear on their own initiative</li>
                        <li>To know the processing status and investigation results</li>
                        <li>To confidentiality of communications</li>
                        <li>To protection measures against retaliation</li>
                        <li>To choose the reporting channel, being able to go to external channels</li>
                        <li>To deletion or anonymization of data after legal deadlines</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div class="column">
                    <h3 class="subsection-title">5.2. Rights of the Affected Person</h3>
                    <ul class="legal-list">
                        <li>To be informed that they are under investigation</li>
                        <li>To honor and privacy</li>
                        <li>To presumption of innocence and to use all valid means for their defense</li>
                        <li>To be heard at any time</li>
                        <li>To submit written allegations</li>
                        <li>To access proceedings, without revealing the informant's identity</li>
                        <li>To rectification of their personal data</li>
                        <li>To protection of their personal data</li>
                        <li>To confidentiality of communications</li>
                        <li>To legal assistance</li>
                        <li>To be informed of the resolution or dismissal of the report</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- 6. SYSTEM MANAGER -->
        <section class="legal-section">
            <h2 class="section-title">6. INTERNAL REPORTING SYSTEM MANAGER</h2>
            <p>
                The Management Body of NUTRIS GROUP has appointed a collegiate body as Manager of the Internal Reporting System
                (Ethical Channel) composed of the following positions:
            </p>
            <ul class="legal-list highlight-list">
                <li>Chief Executive Officer</li>
                <li>Chief Financial Officer</li>
                <li>Quality Director</li>
                <li>Commercial Director</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                The System Manager will carry out their functions independently and autonomously from the rest of the organization's
                bodies and will not receive any instructions in the exercise of their functions.
            </p>
        </section>

        <!-- 7. COMMUNICATION CHANNELS -->
        <section class="legal-section">
            <h2 class="section-title">7. COMMUNICATION CHANNELS</h2>
            <p>The Ethical Channel will be accessible through a specific and separate section on each company's website:</p>
            <div class="contact-links">
                <a href="https://www.nutris.es" target="_blank" class="link-button">
                    <span>www.nutris.es</span>
                    <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 16 16">
                        <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M8.636 3.5a.5.5 0 0 0-.5-.5H1.5A1.5 1.5 0 0 0 0 4.5v10A1.5 1.5 0 0 0 1.5 16h10a1.5 1.5 0 0 0 1.5-1.5V7.864a.5.5 0 0 0-1 0V14.5a.5.5 0 0 1-.5.5h-10a.5.5 0 0 1-.5-.5v-10a.5.5 0 0 1 .5-.5h6.636a.5.5 0 0 0 .5-.5z" />
                        <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16 .5a.5.5 0 0 0-.5-.5h-5a.5.5 0 0 0 0 1h3.793L6.146 9.146a.5.5 0 1 0 .708.708L15 1.707V5.5a.5.5 0 0 0 1 0v-5z" />
                    </svg>
                </a>
                <a href="https://www.roypas.com" target="_blank" class="link-button">
                    <span>www.roypas.com</span>
                    <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 16 16">
                        <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M8.636 3.5a.5.5 0 0 0-.5-.5H1.5A1.5 1.5 0 0 0 0 4.5v10A1.5 1.5 0 0 0 1.5 16h10a1.5 1.5 0 0 0 1.5-1.5V7.864a.5.5 0 0 0-1 0V14.5a.5.5 0 0 1-.5.5h-10a.5.5 0 0 1-.5-.5v-10a.5.5 0 0 1 .5-.5h6.636a.5.5 0 0 0 .5-.5z" />
                        <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16 .5a.5.5 0 0 0-.5-.5h-5a.5.5 0 0 0 0 1h3.793L6.146 9.146a.5.5 0 1 0 .708.708L15 1.707V5.5a.5.5 0 0 0 1 0v-5z" />
                    </svg>
                </a>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- 8. EXTERNAL CHANNELS -->
        <section class="legal-section">
            <h2 class="section-title">8. EXTERNAL REPORTING CHANNELS</h2>
            <p>
                Any natural person may report to the <strong>Independent Authority for the Protection of the Informant (A.A.I.)</strong>
                or to the corresponding regional authorities or bodies, the commission of any actions or omissions that may constitute
                infringements of European Union law, as well as serious and very serious criminal and administrative offenses.
            </p>
        </section>

        <!-- 9. RESPONSIBLE USE -->
        <section class="legal-section">
            <h2 class="section-title">9. RESPONSIBLE USE OF THE ETHICAL CHANNEL</h2>
            <div class="warning-box">
                <p>
                    It is the informant's obligation to make <strong>responsible use of the Ethical Channel</strong>. Under no circumstances
                    should unfounded or malicious reports be made, which may result in legal and/or disciplinary action.
                </p>
                <p>
                    The informant must guarantee, with appropriate evidence, that the data provided is <strong>
                        truthful, accurate,
                        and as complete as possible
                    </strong>.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Under no circumstances will the Channel be used for purposes other than those established herein.
                </p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- 10. DISSEMINATION -->
        <section class="legal-section">
            <h2 class="section-title">10. DISSEMINATION</h2>
            <p>
                The Information System Manager will ensure proper dissemination of this Policy and the existence of the Ethical Channel.
                This Policy is available on the websites of NUTRIS INGREDIENTS and ROYPAS BY NUTRIS along with the respective Ethical Channel.
            </p>
        </section>

        <!-- 11. REVIEW -->
        <section class="legal-section">
            <h2 class="section-title">11. REVIEW</h2>
            <p>
                This Policy will be reviewed annually or when significant changes warrant it, and will be submitted again for approval
                by the Executive Management.
            </p>
        </section>

    </div>

    <!-- Footer -->
    <div class="legal-footer">
        <div class="footer-content">
            <p class="footer-text">
                <strong>Nutris Ingredients, S.L.</strong> | <strong>Roypas by Nutris, S.A.U.</strong>
            </p>
            <p class="footer-text-small">
                Last updated: @DateTime.Now.ToString("MMMM yyyy")
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

